          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1666707383978-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1666707383978-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>peeled garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>roughly chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), <strong>half</strong> your <strong>coriander </strong>(you'll use the rest later), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>chilli paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1666707388995-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1666707388995-x400.jpg",
